com.orchestranetworks.d3
Class D3NodeFactory

java.lang.Object
  com.orchestranetworks.d3.D3NodeFactory

public final class D3NodeFactory
extends Object

Factory for creating a D3 engine depending on the node type chosen (master or slave), which offers D3 administrative functionalities.

To avoid an IllegalArgumentException, verify that the node type is correct before instantiating engines. This can be checked in the property ebx.d3.mode in the EBX5 main properties, or using the methods isMasterNode() and isSlaveNode().

Depending on the type of the node, only some methods may be accessible.

  • If a master node, only createForMasterFromSession(Session) is accessible.
  • If a slave node, only createForSlaveFromSession(Session) is accessible.
  • If a hub, both methods are accessible.
  • If a single node, that is, if D3 is deactivated, none of the methods are accessible.
See Configuring master, hub and slave nodes.

Since:
5.4.2

getCurrentD3Node

public D3Node getCurrentD3Node()
Returns current D3Node of the EBX5 instance. This can be invoked to perform read-only operations without a Session.

If D3 mode is defined as single, then null is returned.
